<div class="method-section">
    <h3>Available RPC Methods</h3>
    
    <h4>Calculator Methods</h4>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>add(a, b)</strong> - Returns sum of two numbers</li>
        <li><strong>multiply(a, b)</strong> - Returns product of two numbers</li>
        <li><strong>divide(a, b)</strong> - Returns division result</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>String Methods</h4>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>reverse_string(text)</strong> - Returns reversed string</li>
        <li><strong>uppercase(text)</strong> - Returns uppercased string</li>
        <li><strong>word_count(text)</strong> - Returns word count</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Storage Methods</h4>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>store_data(key, value)</strong> - Stores key-value pair</li>
        <li><strong>retrieve_data(key)</strong> - Retrieves stored value</li>
        <li><strong>list_keys()</strong> - Returns all stored keys</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="method-section">
    <h3>How it Works</h3>
    <p>This client application communicates with a JSON-RPC 2.0 server running on port 4567. Each form submission generates a JSON-RPC request and displays the formatted response.</p>
    
    <p>The server implements proper JSON-RPC 2.0 protocol including:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Standard request/response format</li>
        <li>Error handling with proper error codes</li>
        <li>Support for both positional and named parameters</li>
        <li>Comprehensive logging</li>
    </ul>
</div>